cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper discusses the unsupervised training of convolutional sparsifying operators or autoencoders from large datasets, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents bounds on errors in the estimated filters, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper investigates the empirical values of the bounds with real data, which involves experiments and data analysis, indicating that it may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
